@page "/chat"
@using FluentUI.Demo.Shared.Pages.Chat.Examples

<h1>Chat</h1>

<p>
    The Chat component allows the user to chat with one or many other users.
    In a chat room, a user can :

    <ul>
        <li>Write a message</li>
        <li>Send documents (audio, video, photo, pdf, doc, docx...)</li>
        <li>Send gift (the user needs to create this part)</li>
        <li>Navigate into views (chat, audio, video, photo, documents, pinned messages...)</li>
        <li>Delete a message</li>
        <li>Edit a message</li>
        <li>Reply to the message</li>
    </ul>

    By default, a SignalRMessageService is provided. For the purpose of the demo, a specific MessageService was build to show how to
    implements your own IMessageService if you don't want to use SignalR.
</p>

